    "As illustrated in Figure 1, these deep learning models have shown state-of-the-art performance across a wide range of neuro-oncology tasks, including but not limited to tumor segmentation, prediction of mutation status for gliomas, and prediction of treatment response [14] [15] [16].",
    "Since brain MRIs are volumetric images, it is natural to employ convolutions along all three dimensions, giving rise to 3D CNNs 17.",
